cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories, as it deals with deformable shape analysis and feature descriptors that are commonly used in correspondence, registration, and retrieval tasks. The paper also discusses a learning scheme for constructing optimal spectral descriptors, which suggests that it may be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper demonstrates its approach on a benchmark dataset, which indicates that it may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
